"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H31241686\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How much do pregnancy symptoms vary?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Symptoms during pregnancy are different from woman to woman. Also, a woman can have different symptoms from 1 pregnancy to the next. Even so, there are certain symptoms that are common during pregnancy.",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      This article discusses symptoms that can happen during a normal, healthy pregnancy.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H264728955\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What symptoms are common early in pregnancy?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Early in pregnancy, sometimes even before a woman knows she is pregnant, common symptoms can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Nausea, with or without vomiting &ndash; This is called &ldquo;morning sickness,&rdquo; but it can happen at any time of the day. For most women, morning sickness lasts only the first few months of pregnancy.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        The breasts getting bigger and feeling painful",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Needing to urinate more often than usual",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Feeling more tired than usual",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Mild cramping in the lower belly",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H264728970\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What symptoms can happen later in pregnancy?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Many different symptoms can happen later in pregnancy. These can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Heartburn or indigestion &ndash; This can feel like a burning feeling in your chest or throat, or pain in your stomach or chest.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Constipation, which means trouble having bowel movements",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Hemorrhoids, which are swollen veins in the rectum that can be painful or itchy",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Stuffy nose and nosebleeds",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Feeling short of breath &ndash; This can get worse slowly as your pregnancy progresses.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Low back pain",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Leg cramps",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Trouble sleeping",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Headaches",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Bleeding from your gums",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Needing to urinate more often than usual or during the night",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Feeling tired",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Your hair getting thicker",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Mild swelling in your feet or ankles",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Numbness or tingling in your hand, foot, or leg",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Varicose veins, which are swollen and twisted veins",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        &ldquo;False&rdquo; contractions &ndash; Contractions are when the uterus tightens. This can cause pain and make the belly feel hard. &ldquo;False&rdquo; contractions, also called &ldquo;Braxton Hicks&rdquo; contractions, do not mean you are in labor. These are different than &ldquo;true&rdquo; contractions, which do mean you are in labor.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Skin changes &ndash; Lots of different skin changes can happen during pregnancy. &nbsp;Some of these include:",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"hyphen-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Skin color changes &ndash; Your palms might turn pink or red. Also, the skin on parts of your body can turn darker. This includes areas on your face or around your nipples (",
"        <a class=\"graphic graphic_picture graphicRef84005 \" href=\"UTD.htm?36/4/36932\">",
"         picture 1",
"        </a>",
"        ).",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        A dark line in the middle of your stomach from your belly button to your pubic area",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Stretch marks &ndash; These look like red lines and are most common on the belly, breast, and thighs.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Spider veins &ndash; These look like small red areas on the skin. They are most common on the neck, face, upper chest, arms, and hands.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Skin tags, which are small growths of normal skin",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H264729008\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       When should I call my doctor or midwife?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;You should call your doctor or midwife if you:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Have bleeding from your vagina",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have fluid leaking from your vagina",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Don&rsquo;t feel your baby move around as much as it used to",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have back or belly pain that doesn&rsquo;t get better with things you can try yourself, such as resting or changing your position",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Feel faint or dizzy",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have heartburn that doesn&rsquo;t get better when you take an antacid medicine",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have a headache that doesn&rsquo;t get better after you rest for an hour in a dark, quiet room",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have pain when you urinate or blood in your urine",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have a fever",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have contractions that get stronger and more frequent",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Have pain when you breathe",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        See dark spots or flashes of light, or have blurry vision",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
